Fig. 1 | Broad benefits of semaglutide. Results from combined analyses of the 
SELECT trial suggest that higher-dose subcutaneous semaglutide has direct 
beneficial effects on atherothrombotic processes. Its weight loss attributes are 
likely more impactful on heart failure (HF) outcomes and in lowering incident 
type 2 diabetes (T2DM), as well as contributing to lower CKD. The intentional 
weight loss will also lower many other outcomes linked to obesity and could 
therefore reduce multimorbidity. MACE, major adverse cardiovascular events.
nature medicine
News & views
SELECT results represent an important advance. However, in persons 
with multimorbidity, anti-obesity medications cannot restore any-
where close to normal health; therefore, prevention strategies must 
be given equal priority for public health.
